# 1 Carat Pear Shaped Diamond Ring: Prices, Settings & Best Picks {{year}}

A 1 carat pear shaped diamond ring at Blue Nile starts at [$3,803 for a natural GIA D-VS1 Ideal cut stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29112328?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) plus a setting, and [$1,006 for a lab grown IGI D-VVS1 Ideal stone](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26932733?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) plus a setting — making the complete ring total $4,200–$4,700 natural or $1,400–$2,500 lab grown depending on the setting style. This guide covers every tier of the 1 carat pear diamond ring: natural GIA stones from $3,803 to $8,272, lab grown stones from $1,006 to $1,548, ring setting costs and styles, the 1.5 carat pear shaped diamond ring tier, and the exact combinations that produce the best ring at every budget.

The 1 carat pear shaped diamond is the most searched size in the pear category. At approximately 8.5×5.7mm, a 1ct pear in a solitaire setting covers significantly more finger length than a 1ct round (6.5mm diameter), creating a ring with a distinctly elongated and elegant silhouette that photographs well and reads as a statement piece on the hand. It is the entry point for buyers who want a pear diamond that makes a clear visual impact.

## TL;DR: 1 Carat Pear Shaped Diamond Ring — Key Numbers

- **Natural GIA 1ct pear diamond:** [$3,803 D-VS1 Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29112328?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (entry) to [$7,578 D-IF Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29054155?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (top). Best value: [$3,849 G-VVS2 Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28866691?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational).
- **Lab grown IGI 1ct pear diamond:** [$1,006 D-VVS1 Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26932733?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (entry) to [$1,548 D-IF Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27731891?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (top). GIA lab certified at same price: [$1,073](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23489206?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational).
- **Ring total (natural):** Stone + setting. Solitaire setting $400–$900. Halo or sidestone $1,100–$3,570. Natural 1ct pear ring total: $4,200–$9,000+.
- **Ring total (lab grown):** $1,400–$3,000 depending on stone grade and setting style.
- **1.5 carat pear shaped diamond ring:** Natural GIA 1.5ct pear rings run approximately $8,000–$16,000 total (stone + setting). Lab grown 1.5ct pear: $2,000–$3,500 total.
- **Priority:** → If budget is $4,000–$5,000 natural, start with the [GIA D-VS1 Ideal at $3,803](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29112328?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and add a solitaire setting. → If budget is under $2,000 lab grown, start with the [IGI D-VVS1 Ideal at $1,006](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26932733?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and a 14K setting.

## 1 Carat Pear Shaped Diamond Ring Price: Natural GIA

A 1 carat pear shaped diamond price at Blue Nile spans from $3,803 to $8,272+ for natural GIA Ideal cut stones, depending on color and clarity grade. The spread is significant: a D-VS1 entry stone at $3,803 and a D-IF at $7,578 share the same carat weight and cut quality but sit $3,775 apart on price. The grade selection for a 1ct pear diamond ring is the single largest variable in the ring's total cost — more than the setting, more than the metal choice.

