d><td>IF</td><td>GIA</td><td><strong>$1,548</strong></td><td>~$2,098</td></tr></tbody></table>

**IGI vs GIA vs GCAL for lab grown 1ct pear rings:**

At 1ct, GIA and IGI lab certified pear diamonds are available at the same price ($1,073 for D-VVS1 Ideal). GIA certification carries greater global name recognition and is the preferred choice when prices match. The GCAL option at $1,508 (D-VVS1) includes the GCAL 8X® cut grade — an optical performance certification not offered by IGI or GIA at this tier. For buyers who want the most rigorous cut documentation available for a lab grown 1ct pear, the GCAL stone is worth the $435 premium over the IGI entry.

For a complete certification comparison and full lab pear pricing from 1ct through 4.5ct+, see the [Lab Grown Pear Diamond Guide](/lab-grown-pear-diamond).

## 1.5 Carat Pear Shaped Diamond Ring

The 1.5 carat pear shaped diamond ring sits between the accessible 1ct tier and the premium 2ct tier. At 1.5ct, a pear diamond measures approximately 10.0×6.7mm at standard L/W ratios — noticeably larger than a 1ct (8.5×5.7mm) and approaching the presence of a 2ct stone (approximately 11.5×7.5mm). The 1.5ct pear is the choice for buyers who want more face-up size than a 1ct provides but are not ready to enter the 2ct natural price tier ($22,605+).

**1.5 carat natural pear shaped diamond ring prices:**
Natural GIA 1.5ct pear diamonds are not consistently available in Blue Nile's inventory. When available, natural GIA D-VS1 Ideal 1.5ct pear diamonds typically run $8,000–$12,000 at current market prices — roughly 2–3× the cost of the same grade at 1ct. This pricing reflects the geometric rarity of natural rough capable of yielding a 1.5ct pear with strong proportions: the heavier the rough weight required, the higher the per-carat premium. For current 1.5ct natural pear inventory, filter Blue Nile's [pear diamond search](https://www.bluenile.com/diamonds/pear-shaped?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) by 1.40–1.60ct to see available stones.

**1.5 carat lab grown pear shaped diamond ring prices:**
Lab grown 1.5ct pear diamonds at Blue Nile sit between the 1ct ($1,006–$1,548) and 2ct ($2,692) price tiers. A lab grown 1.5ct D-VVS1 Ideal pear typically runs $1,500–$2,100. Combined with a solitaire setting at $400–$700, the complete 1.5ct lab grown pear shaped diamond ring total is approximately $1,900–$2,800. For current 1.5ct lab grown pear inventory, see Blue Nile's [lab pear diamond search](https://www.bluenile.com/diamonds/pear-shaped?lab=true&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational).

